text:
Colonial Park: A view northward of the northern half, showing the viaduct at the farthermost end that carries West 155th Street across this grassed slope. Photographers point of vantage is on a line with West 152nd Street.

August 29, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Manhattan: West 152nd Street.

text:
(1) Colonial Park: A view southward of the rocky northern portion of the park. The photographers vantage point is the viaduct on West 155th Street. The buildings on the left, line the east side of Bradhurst Ave., south from West 154th Street (intersection shown).

September 1, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same, one block south. The apartment houses seen on the right are on the west side of Edgecombe Ave.

*September 1, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

Colonial Park: A view of the new playground and wading pool being constructed by the W. P. A. in the northern end of the Park. The photographers vantage point is on a line with W. 153rd Street and shows an elevated viaduct on what would be W. 155th Street.

March 16, 1936.

W. P. A. Photo
Federal Art Project
title: Manhattan: Colonial Park.

text:
Colonial Park: A view northward showing the new swimming pool under construction by the W.P.A. On the right appears buildings that line the east side of Bradhurst Ave., north from and including West 147th Street. This view is taken from the southern extremity of the Park, near 146th Street.

March 16, 1937.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
title: Manhattan: Colonial Park.

text:
Colonial Park: The new swimming pool under construction by the W.P.A. This view is southward from a point near West 147th Street and shows the southern extremity of the Park. Across the background is West 145th Street (southernmost edge) with buildings upon the south side of same, between Bradhurst (left) and Edgecombe (right) Aves. These are numbered 320 to 338 respectively.

March 16, 1937.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
